cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

This paper proposes a novel unsupervised generative clustering approach using deep neural networks, which is a common topic in machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves probabilistic modeling and inference, which suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as likely sub-categories. Lastly, the paper includes experiments on text data, indicating a possible connection to cs.CL (Computation and Language).
